Saudi Arabia to Spend $2.5 Billion on Train Stations, SPA Says

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-02-16T13:44:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-16/saudi-arabia-to-spend-2-5-billion-on-train-stations-spa-says.html
  Saudi Arabia  signed contracts valued
at 9.39 billion riyals ($2.5 billion) for four railway stations
on a line linking Mecca and Medina, the  Saudi Press Agency 
reported, citing the country’s transport minister.  One of the contracts valued at 3.18 billion riyals is for a
station at Mecca, and a second worth 1.56 billion riyals is for
Medina, SPA said, citing Jubara al-Suraisri. A third order is
for a station in  Jeddah  valued at 2.9 billion riyals, and the
fourth is for King Abdullah Economic City in Rabigh for 1.75
billion riyals. Construction will take 30 months, according to
SPA.  Saudi Binladin Group and  Turkey ’s Yapi Merkezi were awarded
the first two orders, and Saudi Oger won the other two, the
Middle East Economic Digest reported on Feb. 1.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
